  "prompt": "How many books does an average person read in a year?",
  "response": "The number of books an average person reads in a year can vary significantly depending on factors such as age, education level, occupation, and personal interests. However, some surveys and studies provide estimates:\n\n1. **Pew Research Center**: A 2021 survey found that the average American adult reads about 12 books per year. However, this number is skewed by avid readers, as the median number of books read per year is 4.\n\n2. **Statista**: A 2020 report indicated that, globally, the average number of books read per year ranges from 4 to 12, depending on the country.\n\n3. **Reading habits**: In countries with high literacy rates and a strong reading culture, such as India and Thailand, the average number of books read per year can be higher, sometimes exceeding 10. In contrast, countries with less emphasis on reading may have lower averages.\n\n4. **Personal variation**: Some people read dozens of books annually, while others may read only one or none at all. Factors such as access to books, time availability, and technology use (e.g., audiobooks or e-books) also influence reading habits.\n\nIn summary, the average person reads between 4 and 12 books per year, but this varies widely depending on individual circumstances and cultural context.",
